{#
  checklist.jinja2
  
  Checklist patterns macro library for generating reusable checklist items.
  Provides reusable macros for checklists, task lists, and verification steps.
  
  Usage:
    {% import 'macros/checklist.jinja2' as checklists %}
    {{ checklists.render_checklist(items, 'Code Review') }}
    {{ checklists.render_numbered_steps(steps, 'Installation') }}
    {{ checklists.render_verification_checklist(checks) }}
#}

{% macro render_checklist(items, title='') -%}
{% if title %}#### {{ title }}

{% endif -%}
```
{% for item in items -%}
- [ ] {{ item }}
{% endfor -%}
```
{%- endmacro %}

{% macro render_numbered_steps(steps, title='') -%}
{% if title %}#### {{ title }}

{% endif -%}
{% for step in steps -%}
{{ loop.index }}. {{ step }}
{% if loop.last == False %}
{% endif %}
{% endfor -%}
{%- endmacro %}

{% macro render_verification_checklist(checks, category='') -%}
#### {% if category %}{{ category }} - {% endif %}Verification Checklist

```
{% for check in checks -%}
- [ ] {{ check }}
{% endfor -%}
```
{%- endmacro %}

{% macro render_code_quality_checklist(language) -%}
#### Code Quality Checklist - {{ language | capitalize }}

{% if language == 'python' -%}
```
Python Code Quality Checklist:
- [ ] All functions have docstrings
- [ ] All public functions have type hints
- [ ] No use of Any without justification
- [ ] No relative imports (use absolute imports)
- [ ] Imports properly grouped and ordered
- [ ] No unused imports
- [ ] No hardcoded configuration values
- [ ] Exception handling uses custom exceptions
- [ ] Resources use context managers
- [ ] No swallowed exceptions (silent pass)
- [ ] Functions are < 50 lines
- [ ] Cyclomatic complexity < 10
- [ ] No magic numbers (use named constants)
- [ ] Variable names are clear and descriptive
- [ ] Database queries use parameterized statements
- [ ] Async/await properly used (no blocking calls)
- [ ] f-strings used for string formatting
- [ ] Dataclasses/pydantic used for data shapes
- [ ] Logging includes context
- [ ] Tests have descriptive names
- [ ] Coverage targets met (80%+ line)
- [ ] Mutation tests pass (80%+ score)
- [ ] Linter (ruff) passes without warnings
- [ ] Type checker (pyright) passes in strict mode
- [ ] No deprecated libraries or patterns
```

