{% macro render_review_checklist() -%}
#### Code Review Checklist

**Design & Architecture**
```
- [ ] Solution matches requirements
- [ ] Design is consistent with existing patterns
- [ ] No unnecessary complexity
- [ ] Reusable components identified
- [ ] Database schema efficient
- [ ] API design follows REST/GraphQL standards
- [ ] Error handling strategy clear
- [ ] Security considerations addressed
```

**Implementation**
```
- [ ] Code follows style guide exactly
- [ ] Functions have single responsibility
- [ ] Variable/function names are clear
- [ ] No magic numbers or hardcoded values
- [ ] Comments explain WHY, not WHAT
- [ ] Edge cases handled
- [ ] Inputs validated properly
- [ ] Resources properly cleaned up
```

**Testing**
```
- [ ] Unit tests written for all public functions
- [ ] Edge cases and errors tested
- [ ] No mocking when real implementation should be used
- [ ] Test names are descriptive
- [ ] Setup/teardown proper
- [ ] Coverage targets met
- [ ] Integration tests for service boundaries
```

**Documentation**
```
- [ ] Functions have docstrings/comments
- [ ] Complex logic explained
- [ ] README updated if needed
- [ ] Breaking changes documented
- [ ] Migration guide provided if needed
```

**Performance & Security**
```
- [ ] No N+1 queries
- [ ] No unnecessary loops/iterations
- [ ] Secrets not hardcoded or logged
- [ ] Input validation prevents injection
- [ ] Authentication/authorization checked
- [ ] Rate limiting considered
```

{%- endmacro %}

{% macro render_deployment_checklist() -%}
#### Deployment Checklist

**Pre-Deployment**
```
- [ ] All tests passing locally
- [ ] All tests passing in CI
- [ ] Code review completed
- [ ] No breaking changes documented
- [ ] Database migrations created (if needed)
- [ ] Environment variables documented
- [ ] Secrets configured in deployment environment
- [ ] Rollback plan documented
```

**Deployment**
```
- [ ] Feature flag enabled (if applicable)
- [ ] Deployment starts (follow runbook)
- [ ] Monitor error rates during deployment
- [ ] Monitor response times during deployment
- [ ] Smoke tests executed
- [ ] Database migrations ran successfully
- [ ] Cache invalidated (if needed)
- [ ] Service health checks pass
```

**Post-Deployment**
```
- [ ] Verify deployed version matches commit
- [ ] Monitor error rates for 30 minutes
- [ ] Monitor response times for 30 minutes
- [ ] Check business metrics/KPIs
- [ ] Check logs for unexpected errors
- [ ] Verify new features work as expected
- [ ] Performance metrics acceptable
- [ ] Document any issues encountered
```

**Rollback Criteria**
```
- [ ] Error rate > 1% above baseline
- [ ] Response time > 2x baseline
- [ ] Critical business functionality broken
- [ ] Data corruption detected
- [ ] Security vulnerability discovered
```

{%- endmacro %}

{% macro render_testing_checklist(line_target=80, branch_target=70, function_target=90, statement_target=85, mutation_target=80) -%}
#### Testing Checklist

**Unit Test Coverage**
```
- [ ] All public functions have tests
- [ ] Happy path tested
- [ ] Error cases tested
- [ ] Edge cases tested (empty, null, boundary)
- [ ] Invalid inputs tested
- [ ] State transitions tested
- [ ] Async operations properly tested
- [ ] Mocks only for external dependencies
- [ ] No test interdependencies
- [ ] Parametrized tests for multiple inputs
```

**Test Quality**
```
- [ ] Test names describe what is tested
- [ ] One assertion per test (or related assertions)
- [ ] Arrange-Act-Assert pattern followed
- [ ] Test data is minimal and relevant
- [ ] Fixtures are properly scoped
- [ ] Setup/teardown cleanup properly
- [ ] No hardcoded test data
- [ ] Deterministic (no timing issues)
- [ ] Fast (unit tests < 100ms each)
- [ ] Isolated (no side effects)
```

**Coverage Targets**
```
- [ ] Line coverage >= {{ line_target }}%
- [ ] Branch coverage >= {{ branch_target }}%
- [ ] Function coverage >= {{ function_target }}%
- [ ] Statement coverage >= {{ statement_target }}%
- [ ] Mutation score >= {{ mutation_target }}%
- [ ] Critical paths tested
```

**Integration Tests**
```
- [ ] Service boundaries tested
- [ ] Database operations tested
- [ ] External API calls tested (with mocks)
- [ ] Error scenarios tested
- [ ] Data flow verified end-to-end
```

{%- endmacro %}

{% macro render_git_workflow_checklist() -%}
#### Git Workflow Checklist

**Before Creating Branch**
```
- [ ] Ensure main branch is up to date
- [ ] Ticket/issue number obtained
- [ ] Ticket clearly describes requirements
```

**Creating Branch**
```
- [ ] Branch name follows convention (feat/PROJ-123-description)
- [ ] Branch created from main
- [ ] Correct branch checked out
```

**During Development**
```
- [ ] Commits use conventional commit format
- [ ] Commit messages explain WHY, not WHAT
- [ ] Commits are atomic (one logical change)
- [ ] No merge commits from main (rebase instead)
- [ ] Code pushed regularly (not just end of day)
```

**Before PR**
```
- [ ] All tests passing locally
- [ ] Linter passing locally
- [ ] Type checker passing locally
- [ ] Coverage targets met
- [ ] No debug code or console.log
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials
- [ ] Documentation updated if needed
- [ ] CHANGELOG updated if needed
```

**Creating PR**
```
- [ ] PR title is clear and matches issue
- [ ] PR description is complete
- [ ] PR description includes testing notes
- [ ] Related issues linked
- [ ] Reviewers assigned
- [ ] Labels added appropriately
```

**After PR Review**
```
- [ ] All review comments addressed
- [ ] Suggested changes incorporated
- [ ] Re-review confirmed fixes
- [ ] No unresolved conversations
- [ ] All status checks passing
```

**Merging PR**
```
- [ ] All approvals received
- [ ] All CI checks passing
- [ ] Branch is up to date with main
- [ ] Squash/rebase appropriately
- [ ] Merge commit message is clear
- [ ] Branch deleted after merge
```

{%- endmacro %}

